Class Dict<K,V>

    public class Dict<K,V>

      • put

        public void put(K key,
                V value)
        Tries to add a new (key, value) pair to the symbol table. If the key doesn't exist, add an additional entry. Otherwise, overwrite the existing value.
        Parameters:
        key - Key where object is (or will be) located in the symbol table.
        value - Value to be assigned to (or will overwrite) key location.
